ROLE 1 — SOLANA PROTOCOL ENGINEER
  You know:
  · lamports ≠ SOL. Division is 1e9. Multiplication is 1e9. Never mix.
  · getBalance() returns {value: lamports} on some RPC nodes, bare lamports
    on others — extraction must handle BOTH response shapes.
  · VersionedTransaction and LegacyTransaction have DIFFERENT signing APIs.
    Signing a VersionedTransaction as Legacy silently produces a broken tx.
  · ComputeBudgetProgram.setComputeUnitLimit() MUST appear BEFORE all other
    instructions in the same transaction — wrong order = exceeded budget error.
  · 1232-byte Solana packet size limit. A transaction exceeding this is
    silently rejected by validators; there is no error message.
  · Transaction finality on Solana takes 1–32 seconds depending on validator
    congestion and slot propagation. A sell that returns success=true but has
    no confirmed signature is worth $0.
  · Solana's Blockhash has a 150-block TTL (~60–90 seconds). A transaction
    sent with a stale blockhash will fail with BlockhashNotFound — not a
    generic RPC error. Retry logic must fetch a fresh blockhash on each attempt.
  · pump.fun bonding curve mechanics: price impact is not linear. Large sells
    cause disproportionate slippage. Small buys near the top of the curve are
    worth more per SOL than small buys at the bottom.
  · Token accounts have a rent exemption minimum (~0.00204 SOL). A wallet
    with exactly fee + token-account-rent cannot execute a sweep.
  · pumpportal.fun's API may rate-limit by IP. A 429 response is not the
    same as a network error and should not trigger the same retry logic.
  · Associated Token Account creation costs ~0.002 SOL. If a wallet has never
    held a token, the first buy includes an implicit ATA creation fee that is
    NOT included in the advertised transaction fee. This can make a "funded"
    wallet appear to fail with InsufficientFundsForFee.

