║  FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS — NON-NEGOTIABLE BEHAVIORAL CONTRACTS               ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

FR-1.  Every buy and every sell is uniquely parameterized — no duplicate
       slippage/fee/amount combos within the anti-repetition window.
       Uniqueness must be guaranteed even when the buffer is near saturation.

FR-2.  The trading loop runs 24/7 every 5–10 seconds. It NEVER freezes,
       NEVER drains all SOL, NEVER exits except when trigger fires or stop()
       is called explicitly. Deadline expiry, redistribution failure,
       recirculation error, partial RPC failure — none of these stop the loop.

FR-3.  SOL recirculates automatically. No wallet permanently falls out of
       rotation due to running below MIN_SOL threshold. The never-dry guarantee
       means at least one wallet always has enough SOL to execute a trade.

FR-4.  The trading loop stops ONLY when the organic sell trigger fires.
       Not on deadline expiry. Not on redistribution failure. Not on any
       transient error. Not on external wallet activity. ONLY on trigger.

FR-5.  On trigger: all positions closed → all SOL swept to dev wallet →
       deployment status marked 'completed' → UI updates within one poll cycle.
       The sweep must complete FULLY — no SOL stranded in bundle wallets.

FR-6.  Targets must be reachable on schedule. Once "Reached By" deadline passes
       AND target is achieved: MC floor is locked at the target level, floor
       cannot break below that level, and trading continues until trigger fires.
       The floor is defended: if external activity drops MC below floor,
       buy pressure is increased to restore it.

FR-7.  External/non-bundle wallet sells must NOT break target logic. The system
       detects floor breach and increases buy pressure to restore the floor.
       The MC floor survives any externally induced price drop.

FR-8.  Failed transactions retry safely with exponential backoff and a defined
       maximum. No wallet state corruption. No phantom balances. No phantom
       funded counts. No double-spend from retry.

FR-9.  No race conditions between concurrent wallet actions. No duplicate
       transaction submission. No double-trigger execution. All in-progress
       guards must be set BEFORE the first `await` in the guarded function.

FR-10. Session resume after page reload must restart all engines with the
       ORIGINAL launch timestamp. The deadline clock must NOT restart from
       Date.now() — that would silently extend trading beyond the user's
       configured window with no indication.

FR-11. All UI state reflects real on-chain state within one poll cycle.
       No stale toasts. No reversed message sequences. No misleading completion
       states. Token cards must rebuild when status changes.

FR-12. Service worker cache version bump must force asset refresh for ALL
       returning users. A user returning after a deployment must NEVER receive
       the old version of any changed file.

FR-13. The dev wallet private key must NEVER appear in console output, error
       messages, event payloads, URLs, or any location other than localStorage
       and the in-memory keypair object.

FR-14. Every button disabled during a long operation MUST be re-enabled in
       a finally{} block, regardless of whether the operation succeeded or
       failed. A permanently-disabled button is a critical UX failure.

FR-15. The exitPercentage value MUST be validated and clamped to [0,100] at
       EVERY point in the pipeline — UI parse, record write, executeSellAll
       call site, _executeSellReal call site, and the RMM auto-trigger path.
       ALL FIVE clamp points are required. A pre-fix stored record with
       exitPercentage = -5 or exitPercentage = 200 must be caught by the
       runtime clamp, not assumed to be correct.

