I1.  exitPercentage ∈ [0, 100] at EVERY point in the pipeline:
     UI parse → record write → executeSellAll → _executeSellReal →
     RMM auto-trigger path. ALL FIVE locations must independently clamp.
     A pre-fix stored record with exitPercentage = -5 passes isNaN(-5) = false
     and must be caught by the runtime clamp.

I2.  TradingEngine._loop exits ONLY when:
     (a) state.running === false (set by stop()), OR
     (b) state.triggerFired === true (set by fireTrigger()).
     Deadline expiry, redistribution failure, recirculation error, and any
     transient RPC error must NOT exit the loop.

I3.  executeSellAll(mint) is idempotent for concurrent calls:
     calling it twice simultaneously must produce exactly one sell pass, one
     sweep, one 'auto-sell-complete' emit, one localStorage write.
     The _sellInProgress guard must be checked BEFORE TradingEngine.stop().

I4.  Deployment record status follows exactly one forward path:
     active → selling → completed.
     The ONLY valid reverse transition: selling → active on cold page reload
     when sell was interrupted. No other backward transition is permitted.

I5.  state.mc ≥ state.mcFloor when allTargetsHit is true.
     `state.mc = Math.max(td.mc, state.mcFloor)` must hold in EVERY code path
     that updates state.mc. The floor is never released.

I6.  knownWallets contains the dev wallet address AND all current bundle wallet
     addresses. No trade from these addresses may count as organic volume.
     knownWallets is rebuilt at least every 60 ticks (5-minute TTL).

I7.  The SOL sweep fires AFTER a minimum 9-second buffer following sell
     confirmation — not sell submission. This buffer is field-tested minimum.
     Do NOT reduce it. Removing it strands sell proceeds.

I8.  The anti-repetition buffer window < hash space for ALL four buffers.
     Every fallback call REGISTERS its result in the buffer.
     No buffer permanently saturates during a 24/7 trading session.

I9.  Every event-bus listener registered inside a trading session
     (mc-pace, and any others) is removed when that session ends —
     whether it ends normally, via trigger, via error, or via stop().
     Stacked listeners compound buy-bias multiplicatively.

I10. The absolute deadline base is computed as:
     `params.launchTime || params.id || Date.now()`
     On resume, params.launchTime comes from the stored record.
     Date.now() is NEVER used as the sole deadline base for a resumed session.

I11. All six version strings (sw.js CACHE_VERSION, package.json version,
     renderer.js FORM_VERSION, both badge emit strings, both features[] arrays)
     are identical and consistent in every delivered pass.

I12. The swept field in 'auto-sell-complete' reflects whether the sweep
     code path actually executed, NOT whether devKey is truthy.
     swept: _sweepAttempted, where _sweepAttempted is set inside `if (devKP)`.

I13. baseMC is persisted to the deployment record immediately upon being latched
     from the first valid poll result. On resume, it is restored from the record
     with a safe default of 0.

I14. mcFloor is persisted to the deployment record immediately upon being locked.
     On resume, if allTargetsHit is true and mcFloor = 0, the system treats this
     as a corrupted state and uses a conservative default (e.g., current organic MC).

I15. All bundle wallets are funded before launchToken creates the on-chain token.
     The bundle buy executes atomically with the launch using pre-funded wallets,
     not wallets funded after launch.

I16. BudgetLedger.init() is called with the correct totalSol value before
     TradingEngine.start() in EVERY code path — initial launch AND session resume.
     A trading engine started with an uninitialized BudgetLedger will use the
     floor value for every trade regardless of the user's configured budget.

I17. No private key material (secretSeed, privateKey bytes, or any derivative)
     appears in console.log, console.error, Error.message, event bus payloads,
     URL parameters, or any outbound network request.

I18. The trading engine never submits a buy or sell transaction while
     state.triggerFired is true. A trigger that fires mid-trade must be checked
     after every await inside the trade execution path.

I19. The total SOL swept to the dev wallet must equal the sum of all sell
     proceeds actually confirmed on-chain, minus per-wallet fee floors.
     Any discrepancy represents stranded funds and must be logged as an error.

I20. lastTradeTs is initialized to Date.now() - (at least 5000ms) at session
     start, never to 0. This prevents the first poll tick from false-triggering
     on historical trade data.

I21. The no-sig trade dedup counter is reset to 0 at the beginning of each
     poll tick, not accumulated across ticks.

I22. _pollInflight uses `delete _pollInflight[mint]` (removes the key entirely)
     in the finally{} block, not `_pollInflight[mint] = false` (which accumulates
     dead keys indefinitely).

I23. Every wallet in the sell loop is checked for non-null address and non-null
     privateKey BEFORE any transaction is constructed with it.

I24. The trigger threshold is computed from `td.mc` (raw on-chain value from
     API) NOT from `state.mc` (which may be floor-clamped). Using state.mc when
     allTargetsHit is true would inflate the trigger target above the raw MC,
     making it permanently unreachable.

I25. The launch button isLaunching flag is reset to false in a finally{} block
     that covers EVERY failure path — IPFS failure, RPC failure, funding failure,
     and any uncaught exception. A stuck isLaunching=true permanently disables
     the launch button until page reload.

I26. Array.isArray() guard is present on EVERY localStorage read that is
     expected to return an array (deployments, clusterAccounts, etc.).
     JSON.parse of corrupted data can return a non-array; calling .forEach,
     .filter, or .map on a non-array throws a TypeError that can crash a poll tick.

I27. Every retryable RPC call fetches a fresh blockhash on each retry attempt.
     The blockhash from attempt 1 is expired by attempt 3 (~60–90 seconds have
     passed). Using a stale blockhash produces BlockhashNotFound rejection.

I28. The per-wallet sweep jitter (random 0–200ms delay between wallet sweeps)
     is present in the sweep loop to prevent RPC rate-limit exhaustion when
     sweeping large clusters simultaneously.

I29. The confirmation count returned by the wallet funding loop reflects only
     confirmed, on-chain-landed batch transfers — not attempted or submitted
     transfers. Phantom funded counts cause the trading engine to start with
     a wallet count that doesn't match the actual funded count.

I30. After onAutoSellFailed fires, the deployment record status is reverted
     from 'selling' back to 'active', _launchesCache is invalidated, and
     refreshTokensView() is called — so the UI correctly reflects that the
     sell failed and the session is still active.

