PHASE 0 — PRE-ANALYSIS: READ THE FIX LOG (MANDATORY)
  Read the entire fix log comment at the top of web-api.js.
  Answer questions Q0-1 through Q0-8 above.
  Do NOT proceed to Phase 1 until all 8 questions are answered.

PHASE 1 — ARCHITECTURE MAPPING
  Map: every module, every public function, every event bus channel (name,
  emitter, listener, payload shape), every localStorage key (name, type,
  default, all readers), every async flow, every state machine, every
  cross-module dependency.
  Identify: which state is ephemeral (memory only) vs persistent (localStorage).
  Identify: which state must survive a page reload and which should not.
  Identify: all assumptions each module makes about other modules.
  Produce: a complete dependency graph. Identify all circular dependencies.
  Do NOT start fixing or cataloguing bugs yet.

PHASE 2 — LINE-BY-LINE STATIC ANALYSIS
  Read every line of every file. Apply the full audit checklist (all 11 sections).
  Apply all 10 lenses to every significant function and every significant fix.
  Apply the 32 bug pattern checks (A through AF) to every code region.
  Do NOT start fixing yet — catalogue everything first.
  Reason: fixes applied before the full catalogue is complete can mask symptoms
  of bugs that haven't been found yet.

PHASE 3 — DYNAMIC SIMULATION
  Trace ALL 200 simulation scenarios. For each:
